For the emission spectrum measurements, pixels on the EMCCD camera are mapped to wavelengths by a third-order polynomial least-squares fit to the emission pattern of calibration samples, including a HeNe cavity without mirrors and organic dyes (Alexa 633, Atto 647N) and fluorescent beads (FluoSpheres, 200 nm diameter, 625/645 nm excitation/emission). Counts in each wavelength bin were adjusted according to the derivative of this fit to account for variations in wavelength bin width. The center of mass of the emission spectrum is given by the weighted normalized sum over all wavelengths λk:2λCM=∑kλkEm(λk)∑kEm(λk)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
